            <section ID="LINK_4456258d-5b7c-442e-9534-e01b66260c44">
               <id root="575d86b1-d3e6-4e22-b20c-30f9e738c1b4"/>
               <code codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" code="34089-3" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Trihexyphenidyl HCl is a synthetic antispasmodic. Each tablet for oral administration, contains 2 mg or 5 mg trihexyphenidyl HCl, each strength also containing as inactive ingredients: magnesium stearate, microcrystalline cellulose, and sodium starch glycolate.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Trihexyphenidyl HCl is a white or slightly off white, crystalline powder, having not more than a very faint odor.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Trihexyphenidyl HCl is the substituted piperidine salt, 1-piperidinepropanol,α-cyclohexyl-α-phenyl-,hydrochloride,(±)-. The structural formula is:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="MM1"/>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20131001"/>
               <component>
                  <observationMedia ID="MM1">
                     <text>This is an image of the structural formula for Trihexyphenidyl HC.</text>
                     <value xsi:type="ED" mediaType="image/jpeg">
                        <reference value="trihexyphenidyltab-1.jpg"/>
                     </value>
                  </observationMedia>
               </component>
            </section>
